00:00:53,354 --> 00:00:55,353
    narrator: table football    
       was first patented       

11
00:00:55,355 --> 00:00:58,189
 by a british inventor in 1923. 

12
00:00:58,191 --> 00:01:00,825
  it became popular throughout  
       europe with leagues      

13
00:01:00,827 --> 00:01:02,861
      forming by the 1950s.     

14
00:01:02,863 --> 00:01:05,797
   a decade later, an american  
     working in west germany    

15
00:01:05,799 --> 00:01:07,766
  brought the game to the u.s., 

16
00:01:07,768 --> 00:01:12,271
  trademarking the german word  
        for it, foosball.       

17
00:01:12,273 --> 00:01:13,806
                     ♪♪         

18
00:01:13,808 --> 00:01:17,175
 in france, the game of foosball
     is known as baby foot.     

19
00:01:17,177 --> 00:01:19,211
      this company produces     
           ready-made,          

20
00:01:19,213 --> 00:01:21,080
  as well as custom-made tables 

21
00:01:21,082 --> 00:01:23,749
          like this one         
    featuring biker players.    

22
00:01:23,751 --> 00:01:27,552
 production begins at a foundry,

23
00:01:27,554 --> 00:01:32,691
       where workers melt       
     down bars of aluminum.     

24
00:01:32,693 --> 00:01:35,794
  an injection-molding machine  
   shoots the molten aluminum   

25
00:01:35,796 --> 00:01:39,732
           into molds           
    in the shape of players.    

26
00:01:39,734 --> 00:01:43,134
   a robot removes the casting  
   from the injection machine.  

27
00:01:43,136 --> 00:01:45,938
  the mold yields four players, 

28
00:01:45,940 --> 00:01:48,206
        each one sporting       
     the manufacturer's name    

29
00:01:48,208 --> 00:01:50,943
   on the front of his jersey.  

30
00:01:50,945 --> 00:01:55,581
 a worker places each casting on
 a press then, with one strike, 

31
00:01:55,583 --> 00:01:58,884
   separates the four players   
   and cuts off excess metal.   

32
00:01:58,886 --> 00:02:01,787
                     ♪♪         

33
00:02:01,789 --> 00:02:03,989
a computer-guided machine drills

34
00:02:03,991 --> 00:02:05,691
      a hole in the center      
         of each player,        

35
00:02:05,693 --> 00:02:11,263
through which the rod will pass.

36
00:02:11,265 --> 00:02:14,567
    then the machine threads    
a hole through the player's back

37
00:02:14,569 --> 00:02:19,672
   for the screw that secures   
     the player to the rod.     

38
00:02:19,674 --> 00:02:22,041
      another machine saws      
       a 2-millimeter gap       

39
00:02:22,043 --> 00:02:24,543
 in the back to allow clearance 
        for a screwdriver       

40
00:02:24,545 --> 00:02:29,648
      to tighten the player     
          onto the rod.         

41
00:02:29,650 --> 00:02:33,585
  once ready, the players move  
 to the foosball table factory, 

42
00:02:33,587 --> 00:02:38,591
      where a worker sprays     
 on a base coat of white paint. 

43
00:02:38,593 --> 00:02:42,161
    once that dries, workers    
  continue painting the players 

44
00:02:42,163 --> 00:02:44,463
  but, now, using an airbrush.  

45
00:02:44,465 --> 00:02:48,567
   they mask the player's body  
     to paint only his head.    

46
00:02:48,569 --> 00:02:52,570
       the company offers       
   a selection of skin tones.   

47
00:02:52,572 --> 00:02:55,140
    then they mask the player   
      with another stencil,     

48
00:02:55,142 --> 00:02:58,143
 covering the skin and exposing 
      the shirt and socks.      

49
00:02:58,145 --> 00:03:01,579
                     ♪♪         

50
00:03:01,581 --> 00:03:03,148
   next, they mask everything   

51
00:03:03,150 --> 00:03:05,584
       except the player's      
         head and feet.         

52
00:03:05,586 --> 00:03:08,920
    a player can be brunette,   
       blonde or redhead.       

53
00:03:08,922 --> 00:03:14,359
 they paint the shoes black then
  the player's eyes and mouth.  

54
00:03:14,361 --> 00:03:17,930
     manufacturers construct    
  the table out of solid beech. 

55
00:03:17,932 --> 00:03:20,199
        a computer-guided       
    milling machine profiles    

56
00:03:20,201 --> 00:03:23,202
      the wood components,      
   drills the required holes,   

57
00:03:23,204 --> 00:03:28,773
 and engraves the company name. 

58
00:03:28,775 --> 00:03:32,377
workers then assemble the parts,
  starting with the four sides, 

59
00:03:32,379 --> 00:03:34,946
    which connect with bolted   
      steel rods and glue.      

60
00:03:34,948 --> 00:03:43,522
                     ♪♪         

61
00:03:43,524 --> 00:03:46,258
    after closing up the ends   
        with wood panels,       

62
00:03:46,260 --> 00:03:48,160
         workers install        
        wood support bars       

63
00:03:48,162 --> 00:03:50,529
      which will reinforce      
         the table and,         

64
00:03:50,531 --> 00:03:54,600
  after a goal, direct the ball 
    to the ball return tray.    

65
00:03:54,602 --> 00:03:57,602
                     ♪♪         

66
00:03:57,604 --> 00:04:00,105
       the table now goes       
        to the paint shop       

67
00:04:00,107 --> 00:04:03,942
   where workers either stain   
  the wood or leave it natural. 

68
00:04:03,944 --> 00:04:06,812
         for this model,        
    they also spray red stain   

69
00:04:06,814 --> 00:04:12,684
        into the recessed       
        stripes and logo.       

70
00:04:12,686 --> 00:04:14,652
       all tables receive       
        a finishing coat        

71
00:04:14,654 --> 00:04:18,490
     of transparent varnish     
      to protect the wood.      

72
00:04:18,492 --> 00:04:21,727
     they install the sloped    
       ball-return panel.       

73
00:04:21,729 --> 00:04:24,863
      when a player scores,     
  the ball rolls down the panel 

74
00:04:24,865 --> 00:04:28,567
to an aluminum ball-return tray.

75
00:04:28,569 --> 00:04:31,669
 after sliding the plywood table
       bottom into place,       

76
00:04:31,671 --> 00:04:34,273
     workers turn the table     
         right-side up,         

77
00:04:34,275 --> 00:04:35,907
  mount the aluminum goal nets, 

78
00:04:35,909 --> 00:04:40,779
      and the scoring units     
       right behind them.       

79
00:04:40,781 --> 00:04:42,848
          then they lay         
      the playing surface,      

80
00:04:42,850 --> 00:04:45,116
       made of green vinyl      
        on pressed wood,        

81
00:04:45,118 --> 00:04:49,455
      on top of the wooden      
          support bars.         

82
00:04:49,457 --> 00:04:54,526
 wood trim around the perimeter 
   holds the surface in place.  

83
00:04:54,528 --> 00:04:57,763
   a worker mounts the players  
   for each line onto a hollow  

84
00:04:57,765 --> 00:04:59,765
      stainless-steel rod.      

85
00:04:59,767 --> 00:05:03,068
 using a template to space them 
 correctly, he bolts each player

86
00:05:03,070 --> 00:05:06,004
           to the rod           
  then attaches a rubber bumper 

87
00:05:06,006 --> 00:05:08,139
   to the players at each end   

88
00:05:08,141 --> 00:05:12,710
  to prevent them from slamming 
     against the side walls.    

89
00:05:12,712 --> 00:05:15,013
      he inserts a narrower     
       stainless-steel rod      

90
00:05:15,015 --> 00:05:17,916
       into the hollow bar      
     to make it telescopic.     

91
00:05:17,918 --> 00:05:22,120
                     ♪♪         

92
00:05:22,122 --> 00:05:24,556
         after preparing        
     eight rods of players,     

93
00:05:24,558 --> 00:05:26,457
     a worker installs them     
          in the table.         

94
00:05:26,459 --> 00:05:30,829
   the telescoping handle end   
  of the rod has spring-loaded  

95
00:05:30,831 --> 00:05:33,532
        bearing that fits       
     in a hole in the table.    

96
00:05:33,534 --> 00:05:37,769
 he secures it from the outside.

97
00:05:37,771 --> 00:05:41,173
 after bolting the opposite end,
  workers protect the top edge  

98
00:05:41,175 --> 00:05:44,877
          of the table          
      with a plastic trim.      

99
00:05:44,879 --> 00:05:47,712
 after threading plastic handles
        to the telescopic       

100
00:05:47,714 --> 00:05:49,047
         end of the rods        

101
00:05:49,049 --> 00:05:52,884
     and mounting the tables    
on four sturdy, solid-wood legs,

102
00:05:52,886 --> 00:05:56,255
       this foosball table      
      is ready for kickoff.     

103
00:05:56,257 --> 00:05:59,424
                     ♪♪         

